{
  "stem": "812.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We became very close with the children in this home and got a very thorough Jewish Hebrew education.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And as I said, it-- we were there in preparation to go to Palestine, but our transport was to be an illegal one.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was 1947, '46, '47, and our transport was to be one similar to that of the No adults were allowed to go along.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was only for children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And my mother, again, she feared-- feared for our lives and for our safety.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "She then decided to make arrangements for us to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We had to get an affidavit again, and-- and our visa and all these papers had to be put in order.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And as my mother made the preparations, she also checked back to Rotterdam to see what had happened to our initial papers from 1939 that we already had intact.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Our passage was booked already in '39.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "It was already paid for.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Fortunately and miraculously, the records were intact.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And our tickets were on record as having been paid for, and we were allowed to use those tickets to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "We had to pay a little additional, even though we were only with three instead of our four, but it was a big help financially.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And now to get an affidavit, that was a little bit more difficult.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Some of our relatives here in the United States were unable to do it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "There were others who couldn't or wouldn't do it, give it to us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "But then that part was very disappointing, because as members of this family knew how industrious and how wonderful and how hardworking my mother was, and we would never be a burden on them.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
